Accepted Files: A header that shows a list of accepted file types (e.g. .txt, .jpeg)
Accepted Ratings: A header that shows a list of accepted ratings per submission (General, Adult, Explicit)
Accepted Type: A header that shows a list of accepted Types (Story, Artwork, etc)
Add Additional Images: Text for a button that allows users to add additional images to the submission
Add Files: Text for a button that users use to start a submission form
Add From Clipboard: Text for a button that users use to copy an image from their clipboard to start a submission form
Additional Images: Header for a section where users add additional images to a submission form
Additional Options: Header for a section where users add/change website options
Adult: A submission rating. Meaning explicit content or something you wouldn't consider SFW
All Ages: Safe for all ages (found in Pixiv additional options)
Animation: A type of submission that is an animation (mostly hidden)
Apply Template: A button that allows users to apply a template from the postybirb sidebar
Artwork: A type of submission that is an image (mostly hidden)
Authentication Failed: Message shown when unable to authenticate a website
Bulk: A mode indicator for editing forms in bulk, rather than single (subject to change in the future)
Bulk Update: Header for dialog that completes a bulk update
Category: Header for website options that can be put into categories (e.g. FurAffinity)
Charge Patrons: A checkbox option for Patreon (whether to charge patrons or not)
Confirm Action: Header for dialog to confirm an action
Default Description: Generic description used by all websites unless changed elsewhere
Default Tags: Generic tags used by all websites unless changes elsewhere
Shortcuts: Text for a button that shows description help and shortcuts
Add Files Button Tooltip: A tooltip that appears when you hover over the Add Files button.
Emergency Stop: Button that immediately stops the app posting and restarts the app
Extreme: A submission rating. Refers to adult and anything that could be considered offensive
General: A submission rating. Refers to anything SFW.
In minutes: Denotes that the form field is counted in minutes (1 = 1 minute)
Mature: A submission rating. Refers to things not quite SFW, but not necessarily explicit in nature.
Music: Submission type for music/audio submissions (mostly hidden)
Notify: Common website option. Whether or not to notify watchers (DA, IB, Weasyl)
Paused until: Posting submission is waiting for some timer to occur
Post Interval: Time in between each submission (in minutes) manually set by user in Settings
JournalBirb dashboard: General description for JournalBirb shown in dashboard
Queued: Submission state of being in queue
Schedule: Button text to schedule a submission to post at a certain time
PostyBirb dashboard: General description for PostyBirb shown in dashboard
Scheduled: Header for section that displays scheduled submissions
Select Blog: Tumblr option header for selecting blog
Select Folder: Generic select header for selecting folder(s)
Sexual Content: A checkbox for Pixiv (maybe DA) options that spedcifies if the content has sexual content
Skips incomplete forms: Generic warning tooltip for Save All button
Sta.sh Only: DeviantArt option (marked for removal in the future)
Status: FurryNetwork website option to denote status of submission
Story: Submission type for text/story submissions (mostly hidden)
Time to post: The time to post a submission (the schedule time)
Title: Title of a submission
Unauthorize: To revoke access to an authorized website (essentially to logout)
Unposted: Submission status of a submission that has not been posted
Use Default: To use a default setting (in this case description)
Use Title: Tumblr website option to display the title
